The molecular formula of oxazinan-3-one is C₅NH₈O. Breaking down the full chemical name, 2-(3-amino-2-methylpropyl)oxazinan-3-one, we can identify the following atoms:

- Carbon (C): 8 atoms
- Nitrogen (N): 2 atoms
- Hydrogen (H): 13 atoms
- Oxygen (O): 1 atom

Adding up the total number of atoms present in 2-(3-amino-2-methylpropyl)oxazinan-3-one, we find that there are 24 atoms in total.
